---
import BaseLayout from '../../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
import Breadcrumb from '../../components/Breadcrumb.astro';
import AnswerContent from '../../components/AnswerContent.astro';

const answerContent = `
Neither ChatGPT nor Claude is universally better in April 2026. [ChatGPT](/tools/chatgpt/) is better as an all-purpose assistant. [Claude](/tools/claude/) is better for careful writing, long-context reasoning, and many developer workflows.

ChatGPT wins on breadth. It bundles GPT-5.5, image generation, browsing, voice, Codex, agents, file analysis, and a mature consumer ecosystem. If you want one subscription that covers most personal and business tasks, ChatGPT is the easier default.

Claude wins when the output needs more restraint and structure. It is especially strong for long documents, nuanced writing, careful analysis, and code work through [Claude Code](/tools/claude-code/). Teams that value conservative behavior and transparent long-context workflows should test Claude first.

The decision is mostly workflow fit. Choose ChatGPT for multimodal work, images, voice, Codex, and broad assistant coverage. Choose Claude for writing quality, long-context analysis, and codebase reasoning. Many power users keep both because they solve different jobs.
`;

const answerLD = JSON.stringify({
  '@context': 'https://schema.org',
  '@type': 'Article',
  headline: 'ChatGPT vs Claude: Which Is Actually Better (2026)?',
  author: { '@type': 'Organization', name: 'aipedia.wiki Editorial', url: 'https://aipedia.wiki/about/editorial/' },
  publisher: { '@id': 'https://aipedia.wiki/#organization' },
  datePublished: '2026-04-16',
  dateModified: '2026-04-27',
  mainEntityOfPage: 'https://aipedia.wiki/answers/chatgpt-vs-claude-which-is-better/',
});
---

<BaseLayout title="ChatGPT vs Claude: Which Is Actually Better (2026)?" description="ChatGPT wins on breadth, multimodal tools, Codex, and agents; Claude wins on careful writing, long-context work, and many developer workflows.">
  <script type="application/ld+json" set:html={answerLD} />
  
  <Breadcrumb items={[{ label: 'Answers', href: '/answers/' }, { label: 'ChatGPT vs Claude: which is better?' }]} />

  <article class="max-w-[var(--site-narrow-max)] mx-auto py-[var(--site-content-gap)]">
    <h1 class="text-2xl sm:text-3xl font-bold text-[var(--text-primary)] mb-[var(--site-card-gap)]">ChatGPT vs Claude: which is better?</h1>
    <div class="flex items-center gap-[var(--site-card-gap)] text-sm text-[var(--text-muted)] mb-[var(--site-content-gap)]">
      <a href="/about/editorial/" class="inline-flex items-center gap-1.5 no-underline hover:underline">
        <span class="text-[var(--text-secondary)]">aipedia.wiki Editorial</span>
      </a>
      <span aria-hidden="true">·</span>
      <time datetime="2026-04-27" class="text-[var(--accent-success)]">Updated April 2026</time>
    </div>

    <AnswerContent content={answerContent} />

    <div class="mt-[var(--site-section-gap)] pt-[var(--site-content-gap)] border-t border-[var(--border)] text-sm text-[var(--text-muted)]">
      <p>This answer reflects flagship models and pricing as of April 2026. See our <a href="/about/scoring/" class="text-[var(--accent-primary)] no-underline hover:underline">scoring methodology</a> for how we evaluate tools.</p>
    </div>
  </article>
</BaseLayout>
